INSERT INTO `wefi_success_stories` VALUES (1,'','<p style=\'margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;line-height:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:\"Cambria\",serif;margin:0in;text-align:justify;\'><span style=\'font-size:13px;font-family:\"Georgia\",serif;color:black;\'>IronOne Technologies &amp; BoardPAC, are software design and development company located in Sri Lanka, Malaysia, Singapore, South Africa, Australia, India and USA. At present, IronOne &amp; BoardPAC with 102 employees is an award-winning company with quality standards such as the ISO27001, ISO9001, Stevie Awards and Great Places to Work Awards which are especially for out-sourced IT services and pre-built IT products recognized &nbsp;in Asia Pacific which includes countries such as Malaysia, Singapore, India, Hong Kong, Nepal, Bangladesh, Pakistan, Indonesia, Australia also Africa and in recent times expanded to the US. The company has experience in servicing large corporate clients and offers customized methodologies for software services through its offshore development center based in Sri Lanka. The company also offers several pre-built software solutions enabling clients to achieve their requirements faster. IronOne and BoardPAC has been expanding its business to the US market and today it provides services to clients in the South East Asian market, where the growth of the IT software market is the highest in the world. IronOne and BoardPAC provides a range of solutions including Board Management Software, Capital markets Stock trading platform software, Banking Business intelligence software and a specialized niche mobile application development unit that services high end US clientele.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;line-height:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:\"Cambria\",serif;margin:0in;text-align:justify;\'><span style=\'font-size:13px;font-family:\"Georgia\",serif;color:black;\'>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;line-height:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:\"Cambria\",serif;margin:0in;text-align:justify;\'><span style=\'font-size:13px;font-family:\"Georgia\",serif;color:black;\'>A self-described firefighter, who thrives at problem solving, Ms. Lakmini Wijesundera has escalated to the top of the IT field as CEO and co-founder of IronOne Technologies and BoardPAC. After graduating from the Imperial College in UK, Lakmini launched the enterprise in 2006 at Lakmini&rsquo;s mother&rsquo;s garage &ndash; along with her friend current Chairman, Mr. Sanje Widyaratne who was based in the US. Since then, the company achieved organic and huge growth over the decade. Born with &ldquo;a passion to create&rdquo;, she has launched (amongst other things) 3 flagship products; <em>ATRAD</em> &ndash; a real-time online stock trading system used by 70+% of Sri Lankan stockbrokers; <em>BoardPAC</em> &ndash; a revolutionary paper-less way for Board Directors to securely access board/committee papers and provide approvals; and <em>Infosense&nbsp;</em>&ndash; an banking specific analytics software to provide decision support to Boards and senior executives in the banking sector , that is a sought-after product by large corporations globally and with coverage across 20 countries at present.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;line-height:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:\"Cambria\",serif;margin:0in;text-align:justify;\'><span style=\'font-size:13px;font-family:\"Georgia\",serif;color:black;\'>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;line-height:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:\"Cambria\",serif;margin:0in;text-align:justify;\'><span style=\'font-size:13px;font-family:\"Georgia\",serif;color:black;\'>Lakmini highlights the importance of improving financial ecosystem for startups. &ldquo;There were no initial investors&rdquo;, explains Lakmini . &ldquo;We just put down our personal monies and decided to get investors thereafter as and when needed. Our products don&rsquo;t yield instant returns and progress can be painstakingly slow.&rdquo; &nbsp;She further added that &ldquo; Since then, I have observed statistics and surveys that show that we are not alone in this approach, and that a majority of startups in the South Asia region specially in Sri Lanka share similar experiences in terms of initially boot-strapping with personal cash and then expanding next with bank lending to spurt the growth before taking the consideration of equity investments&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;line-height:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:\"Cambria\",serif;margin:0in;text-align:justify;\'><span style=\'font-size:13px;font-family:\"Georgia\",serif;color:black;\'>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;line-height:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:\"Cambria\",serif;margin:0in;text-align:justify;\'><span style=\'font-size:13px;font-family:\"Georgia\",serif;color:black;\'>Lakmini has not felt discriminated because of her sex. &ldquo;Maybe I&rsquo;m na&iuml;ve, but I&rsquo;ve never been conscious of being a woman in a male-dominated arena. I&rsquo;m just &lsquo;me&rsquo;. I let my work speak for itself and always come out on top. Whatever struggles I&rsquo;ve faced, my industry counterparts have faced too &ndash; it&rsquo;s not a gender thing.&rdquo; She further added &ldquo;the challenges we have in becoming globally recognized brands and gaining such acceptance and overcoming cultural differences with other countries when we start out in South Asia itself is a challenge that is common to both males and females and therefore I believe that such a challenge drowns all other challenges&rdquo;.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;line-height:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:\"Cambria\",serif;margin:0in;text-align:justify;\'><span style=\'font-size:13px;font-family:\"Georgia\",serif;color:black;\'>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;line-height:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:\"Cambria\",serif;margin:0in;text-align:justify;\'><span style=\'font-size:13px;font-family:\"Georgia\",serif;color:black;\'>Innovation, she says, is the main theme at the office. Technical and managerial staff are encouraged to take decisions, solve issues and innovate as they create solutions and products. Lakmini with a focused strategic mindset plans to expand the business and streamline operations to maximize profits. The company is also looking at capital injection to facilitate further growth of the business. In the months ahead, Lakmini is looking to get more highly technical expertise, and delegating a lot of her work to the next level team members. That way, &ldquo;I can concentrate on what I&rsquo;m best at for the benefit of the organization &ndash; strategizing and creating.&rdquo; She further added &ldquo;This method also nutures everyone in the company to continue to expand their experiences and grow rather than getting stuck in their present roles&rdquo;.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;line-height:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:\"Cambria\",serif;margin:0in;text-align:justify;\'><span style=\'font-size:13px;font-family:\"Georgia\",serif;color:black;\'>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\'margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:.5in;line-height:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:\"Cambria\",serif;margin:0in;text-align:justify;\'><span style=\'font-size:13px;font-family:\"Georgia\",serif;color:black;\'>Lakmini believes in &ldquo;achieving the seemingly impossible&rdquo;, and in terms of the key flagship products <em>ATrad</em> and <em>BoardPAC</em>, she is working towards gaining visible and impactful global market share and presence.</span></p>','Ms. Lakmini Wijesundera',35,0,'','','IronOne Technologies & BoardPAC  ','0000-00-00 00:00:00','https://i.ibb.co/WpwsWX5/lakmini-w-int.jpg',''),(2,'Promoting entrepreneurship and innovation.','<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.295;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Georgia;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">zMessenger Private Limited provides Digital Marketing services and advertising technology solutions. At present, the company employs 100+ staff and its annual turnover is $6 Mn. Founded in 2003 as Sri Lanka&rsquo;s first mobile marketing company headquartered in Colombo, the firm currently offers full spectrum digital and mobile marketing programs and SMS-based audience engagement applications to electronic media stations. The company now has advanced their portfolio of services with the introduction of AdTech (Advertising technology) platform which helps driving high return on investment (ROI) driven digital advertising campaigns with advance audience analytics. &nbsp;The company&rsquo;s value-added services business arm now provides Over the Top (OTT) content delivery services for data users with its own Subscription Video On Demand (SVOD) platform. &nbsp;Its software services comprise software research and development, product design and development, design consulting, product migration and re-engineering, full product/software testing cycle and quality assurance, and product maintenance and support.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><br></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.295;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Georgia;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Co-founded by Ms. Jayomi Lokuliyana and her partners Mr. Janaka Rupasinghe and Mr. T. Dushyanthan, the outfit started life in 2003, in the tech incubator of the Sri Lanka Institute of Information Technology (SLIIT) known as ConceptNursery. Here, IT startups shared rent, office space, and big dreams; fueling one another. &ldquo;We were at the right place, at the right time&rdquo;, says Jayomi who then struck-up a partnership that paved the way for zMessenger.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><br></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.295;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Georgia;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">The first years of the business were very tough and constrained due to the lack of capital. &ldquo;Being a tech startup, no one was willing to lend us the seed capital. We were the first mobile marketing company in the country, and there was no benchmark to prove that this was a viable business sector&rdquo;. &nbsp;She had to struggle to build credibility for a once unheard of sector of the IT industry &ndash; particularly amongst lending institutions. Having faced rejection, Jayomi and her business partner had to appeal to their families for help for initial capital. A distant relative from Norway made the investment needed to go forward. Nevertheless, in the first five years business growth was constrained due to lack of capital to take ideas to market.</span></p>\r\n<p><br></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.295;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Georgia;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">In 2008, zMessenger&rsquo;s rapidly developing innovations caught the attention of a foreign investor from Indonesia who injected capital into the business (which enabled the company to increase its platforms) and brought in market development expertise. The equity partner also helped the outfit make the important shift from B2B mobile marketing solutions, to mobile VAS; a product diversification that has reaped big returns. The team gained exposure to the advanced tech trends in the Indonesian market &ndash;which was two years ahead of Sri Lanka at the time &ndash; as well as the overall dynamics of the South East Asian digital market.</span></p>\r\n<p><br></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.295;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Georgia;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Over the years, the CEO says she has encountered barriers from certain sectors of the Telecom industry, government, and banking. &ldquo;Knowing that women possess lesser assets than men, they insist on asking for disproportionate collateral. Such barriers are even worse for rural lady entrepreneurs&rdquo; she says. What&rsquo;s more, approvals move far too slowly to satisfy the lightning-speed pace of the technology industry, resulting in missed opportunities. There is also an important need for business incubators to train-up young entrepreneurs on financial literacy, such as on business valuation and making investor pitches. Jayomi explains that IT startups are so focused on their technical areas that they don&rsquo;t acquire the necessary skills to help their businesses grow. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><br></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.295;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Georgia;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Today, zMessenger is at the top of its game, having planned, created and executed over 2000 digital marketing and campaign strategies for global brands like Unilever, Chevron and Samsung. Currently interacting with over 10 million mobile users, the enterprise is always exploring for new market spaces to occupy and to diversify into, in the digital domain. &ldquo;AdTech and Programmatic Advertising are very active now&rdquo;, declares Jayomi. &ldquo;We&rsquo;re working on first AdTech platform with advance analytics for Digital Advetising for ever demanding video content streaming.&rdquo; &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><br></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:Georgia;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Jayomi also mentioned on the new venture which is &lsquo;Mymed&rsquo;, &nbsp;a company based on the key objective to make healthcare products and services easily available to public. &nbsp;MyMed.lk was created with the public in mind. By caring for the health of the people, MyMed.lk has now become an integral part of customers&rsquo; advisory services and medicine purchase journey. Staying true to its brand promise, &lsquo;Trust, Convenience and Care&rsquo;, Mymed has launched many initiatives to uphold their brand promise. &nbsp;Mymed being accredited by Sri Lanka Standard Institute as a COVID-19 controlled business ensures that all the deliveries are handled per high level of hygiene and safety practices. Additionally, Mymed offers contact less delivery to ensure the safety of all customers.&nbsp;</span></p>','Ms. Jayomi Lokuliyana',48,0,'','https://www.zmessenger.com/','CEO, zMessenger','0000-00-00 00:00:00','https://i.ibb.co/dWKBhbd/jayomi-l-int.png',''),(4,'','','Mrs. Nelum Devi',28,5,'','','Entrepreneur','2021-02-20 14:02:16','https://i.ibb.co/Z1pX008/Screenshot-2021-04-02-021700-1.png','https://www.adb.org/news/videos/empowering-women-entrepreneurs-sri-lanka-nelum-devi-s-story'),(5,'','','Mrs. Ruchirani Munasinghe',25,1,'','','Entrepreneur','2021-02-20 18:25:31','https://i.ibb.co/fCjK9rJ/ruchirani-ext.png','https://www.adb.org/news/videos/empowering-women-entrepreneurs-sri-lanka-ruchirani-munasinghes-story '),(6,'','','Ms. Indumala Rajapaksha',0,0,'','','Entrepreneur','2021-04-01 23:21:41','https://i.ibb.co/7g3tFxT/indumala-harasgama.png','https://www.adb.org/news/videos/empowering-women-entrepreneurs-sri-lanka-indumala-s-story'),(7,'','','Mrs. Pradeepa Nilanthi',0,0,'','','Entrepreneur','2021-04-01 23:40:07','https://i.ibb.co/9qYQTFz/pradeepa-n-ext.png','https://www.adb.org/news/videos/empowering-women-entrepreneurs-sri-lanka-pradeepa-nilanthis-story');
